<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-03-08T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-03-08T16:00:00-05:00" n="569" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d569">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/17368</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-08T14:00:00-07:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 8, 1916, 2 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Villa forces south of Columbus have not been attacked and are not being
                            pursued, according to private admissions in Juarez, because of
                            insufficient troops under Juarez command and failure of detachments from
                            Chihuahua.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cobb</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>